Yusra Ghannouchi is the international spokesperson for the Tunisian Ennahdha Party and a daughter of the party founder, Rashid Ghannouchi. She returned to Tunisia with her father in 2011 after the protests that led to the removal of the Ben Ali government. She is active in bridge building between different communities, interfaith dialogue and advocacy for the rights of Muslim women and has lectured internationally on these issues.
